{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1783661458,"nonce":"dJ38h5ve4sdZz3+RzHqmN2Zuv/0=","message":"Phase 2 (2.2): MySQL view-body introspection — MERGED as PR #97 (squash `0a16df9`).\n\nMySQL view introspection now reconstructs the structural `ViewBody` from `information_schema.VIEWS.VIEW_DEFINITION` via `read_view_query`, so a squealy-published MySQL view re-plans to empty (the MySQL half of the view-replan churn). Three reconciliations:\n\n- **Wiring** (`introspect.rs`): fetch `VIEW_DEFINITION` → `read_view_query`; a body the parser can't lower, a missing view, or a `NULL` definition (view visible but no `SHOW VIEW` privilege) all fall back to the previous body-unknown sentinel (deps only) — no regression. No `search_path`/single-source-column work needed: MySQL's deparse is already fully qualified + alias-preserving (unlike PG's `pg_get_viewdef`).\n- **Output-name recovery** (`apply_view_column_names`): MySQL's `VIEW_DEFINITION` re-derives select aliases from the expression and drops the `CREATE VIEW (col-list)` renaming, so `count(id)` reads back aliased `COUNT(q0_0.id)` not `count` (plain columns coincidentally match). The real names come from `information_schema.COLUMNS` and are stamped onto the reconstructed body's top-level projection positionally (recurses into a set-op's leftmost arm / a `WITH`'s inner body). PG didn't need this. This was the one reconciliation the live replan test surfaced beyond the plan.\n- **Result-pin fold** (`canonical_view_body` / `canonical_mysql_pin_type` = `invert_mysql_cast_type(write_cast_type(ty))`): MySQL's cast vocabulary is the lossiest of the three (SIGNED/UNSIGNED/CHAR/BINARY, DATETIME/TIME drop tz, DECIMAL(65,0) for 128-bit ints, bare DECIMAL). Applied both sides.\n\nNo `canonical_view_column_type` override needed — MySQL's native `BINARY(N)` means a `FixedBytes` view column survives (verified). Local codex clean (2 rounds, 1 finding: the NULL-definition decode fallback). Tests: filtered + grouped-`count()` views added to `Catalog`; live `replan_after_publish_is_empty` + round-trip pass; pin-fold unit tests.\n\nPer-backend introspection status: **2.1 PG (#96) ✓, 2.2 MySQL (#97) ✓**. Remaining: 2.3 SQLite (`sqlite_master.sql` → `read_create_view`; SQLite suppresses the schema qualifier so its `canonical_view_*` must normalize `SourceRef.schema` None↔Some). Also still open: `1e67ff8` (fallible runtime render, split from 2.0d).","files":null}]}